&lt;NEW&gt;

It is indeed possible that TUSCON did not know much about the
decorated Warrior-General that was MAGMATRON, since he probrably came
online after MAGMATROn had disappeared.

He was a PREDACON and arose ouf of the ashes of the ancient
Decepticons. He was in general known, at least to the few they did
know him, to be a warior of great cunning and skill. He was both
highly intelligent, with a very long military background. He was a
gifted tactical genius and yet capable of great savagery as well. Some
thought he had been defeated in some battle, perhaps assasinated by an
up and comming Predacon. But yet here he was finally resurfacing after
five decades or more here on old Earth.

------------------

GUILEDART and his two henchmen led TUSCON to what atfirst appeared to
be a cliff face positioned on the side of a mountain side. It was as
if some great force had sheered off a side of the mountain towards the
bottom, leaving a smooth and very steep wall leading up perhaps
several hundred feet. However that is not the direction that TUSCON
was being led.

As the the path they were on came up and over and met the cliff face
they could turn and see a huge valley opening up before them, a large
river running down from the surrounding mountains, along with large
trees and other assorted folliage.

GUILEDART pulled out a strange device and oriented it just off the
path ahead ihn a strange and obsure clearing then activated it. As he
did so a shimmering energy field appeared looking very much like a
door, it was perhaps a thousand yards or so ahead of them.

&quot;There.&quot; GUILEDART said as he pointed at it.

They continued walking on, HARDHEAD and HYDRA leading TUSCON with
weapons still drawn. They seemed to have little or no regard for
TUSCON&#39;s injured state as they moved quickly over the broken ground
that quickly sloped downward.

